{"_id":"h6nIGfpF8ugtVjVT","name":"Automator","permission":{"default":0,"55oRMeK8J5d3pvei":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>An automator is a catch all type of gadget that exists to automate basic actions. Such as opening doors or lighting a gaslamp. Automators do not possess much agility, but are still capable of doing basic functions.</p>\n<p>Consider the automator a 1 Hit Die construct with average hit points and hardness for a gadget, size of Tiny or small (chosen at the time of the creation), no ability scores except a Strength and Dexterity score of 10, an AC equal to 10 + 1/2 your ranks in Craft (mechanical), a bonus to saves equal to +0, movement speed of 0, and a base attack bonus of 0. It possesses no senses or auditory functions. Automators possess no magic item or augment slots. Automators cannot perform any action that requires an attack roll or combat action, but may perform ability and skill checks (this is left ultimately to the GM&#8217;s discretion).</p>\n<p>The exact shape of an automator is determined at the time of creation. An automator can possess up to 2 limbs that must be inbuilt with whatever they wield or use. For instance an automator that can open or close a single door can take the form of a simple box with a pulley that attaches to a door. An automator may be created with only 1 limb in order to increase its movement speed to 5 feet. Automators can work in tandem to accomplish multiple smaller tasks that amount to a singular larger task. You can create and maintain a number of automators equal to your practitioner modifier as one gadget.</p>\n<p>Each charge allows an individual automator to function for 8 hours (which can be used in non-consecutive 1 hour increments).</p>\n","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[["Gadget"]],"activation":{"cost":1,"type":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","long":null},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null,"autoDeductCharges":true,"autoDeductChargesCost":"1"},"measureTemplate":{"type":"","size":"0","overrideColor":false,"customColor":"","overrideTexture":false,"customTexture":""},"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","critConfirmBonus":"","damage":{"parts":[],"critParts":[],"nonCritParts":[]},"attackParts":[],"formula":"","ability":{"attack":null,"damage":null,"damageMult":1,"critRange":20,"critMult":2},"save":{"dc":0,"type":"","description":""},"effectNotes":"","attackNotes":"","soundEffect":"","changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noStr":false,"noDex":false,"oneInt":false,"oneWis":false,"oneCha":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[],"charges":[]},"featType":"combatTalent","associations":{"classes":[]},"showInQuickbar":false,"abilityType":"none","crOffset":"","attack":{"parts":[]},"sphere":"Tech","identifiedName":"Automator"},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.aXmiiA7v9kJbetit"},"spheres-sheet":{"sphere":"SpheresSheet.SphereTech"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"h8qD11pPwLfGOE5C","name":"Tricky Traps","permission":{"default":0,"55oRMeK8J5d3pvei":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>A creature that fails its Reflex save to avoid this snare is subject to a dirty trick maneuver as if the trap successfully beat their CMD. This counts as you performing the dirty trick for the purposes of Scoundrel sphere abilities that depend on you triggering the dirty trick. Creatures targeted by this trap get a +1 circumstance bonus on their saving throw for each size category they are larger than Medium.</p>\n","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[["Snare"]],"activation":{"cost":1,"type":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","long":null},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null,"autoDeductCharges":true,"autoDeductChargesCost":"1"},"measureTemplate":{"type":"","size":"0","overrideColor":false,"customColor":"","overrideTexture":false,"customTexture":""},"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","critConfirmBonus":"","damage":{"parts":[],"critParts":[],"nonCritParts":[]},"attackParts":[],"formula":"","ability":{"attack":null,"damage":null,"damageMult":1,"critRange":20,"critMult":2},"save":{"dc":0,"type":"","description":""},"effectNotes":"","attackNotes":"","soundEffect":"","changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noStr":false,"noDex":false,"oneInt":false,"oneWis":false,"oneCha":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[],"charges":[]},"featType":"combatTalent","associations":{"classes":[]},"showInQuickbar":false,"abilityType":"none","crOffset":"","attack":{"parts":[]},"sphere":"Trap","identifiedName":"Tricky Traps"},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.3v2EyY8F8wPwfjLp"},"spheres-sheet":{"sphere":"SpheresSheet.SphereTrap"}},"img":"modules/spheres-sheet/icons/spheres/trap.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"hAEhcOVFNFvhmhD0","name":"Targe Riposte","permission":{"default":0,"55oRMeK8J5d3pvei":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You can use the hand wielding a light shield to also wield a light or one-handed weapon, as if it were a buckler, but you take a -2 penalty on attack rolls (instead of -1). If the hand wielding the light shield is wielding a weapon from the close or light blades fighter weapon group, you only take a -1 penalty on attack rolls. Whenever you would attempt a melee attack with a shield bash, you may instead attempt a melee attack with a light or one-handed weapon from the close or light blades fighter weapon groups wielded in your shield hand.</p>\n<p>You may take this talent a total of twice. If taken a second time, whenever you would attempt a melee attack with a shield bash, you may instead attempt a melee attack with any light or one-handed weapon (not just those from the close or light blades fighter weapon groups) wielded in your shield hand.</p>\n","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"activation":{"cost":1,"type":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","long":null},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null,"autoDeductCharges":true,"autoDeductChargesCost":"1"},"measureTemplate":{"type":"","size":"0","overrideColor":false,"customColor":"","overrideTexture":false,"customTexture":""},"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","critConfirmBonus":"","damage":{"parts":[],"critParts":[],"nonCritParts":[]},"attackParts":[],"formula":"","ability":{"attack":null,"damage":null,"damageMult":1,"critRange":20,"critMult":2},"save":{"dc":0,"type":"","description":""},"effectNotes":"","attackNotes":"","soundEffect":"","changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noStr":false,"noDex":false,"oneInt":false,"oneWis":false,"oneCha":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[],"charges":[]},"featType":"combatTalent","associations":{"classes":[]},"showInQuickbar":false,"abilityType":"none","crOffset":"","attack":{"parts":[]},"sphere":"Shield","identifiedName":"Targe Riposte"},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.nBlDVKZH9iV50pPy"},"spheres-sheet":{"sphere":"SpheresSheet.SphereShield"}},"img":"modules/spheres-sheet/icons/spheres/shield.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"hEZZB0aF7e9FaPV0","name":"Advanced Cohorts","permission":{"default":0,"55oRMeK8J5d3pvei":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Leadership sphere, (cohort) package, Diplomacy 5 ranks.</p>\n<p>You may recruit intelligent (Int greater than 2) creatures of any type into your service, though creatures of a different type impose a +10 increase to their recruit DC. Creatures so recruited use their normal statistics and equipment.</p>\n<p>Unlike normal cohorts, advanced cohorts that are not of normal player races are unlikely to be found in settlements, though may be encountered over the course of the campaign; finding a particular creature may require a seperate adventure to seek out and ally yourself with them. Monstrous creatures often have very different perspectives and goals than common adventurers, so may be even more likely to have the cohort relationship be transitory.</p>\n<p>Creatures recruited with this talent cannot have a CR greater than half your ranks in Diplomacy (round down as usual). Use the minimum required Diplomacy ranks to recruit such a creature in place of its Hit Dice for determining the number of Hit Dice required from your Hit Dice pool. Advanced cohorts start with whatever gear is appropriate per their creature entry or situation. As usual, the cohort must be compensated for any equipment that is lost. Equipment you provide to an advanced cohort is not factored into their CR calculation.</p>\n<p>Creatures that advance by class levels may advance as a cohort, using cohort professions, whenever a cohort would normally be allowed to gain Hit Dice. Otherwise, they may advance by class, using their new CR to determine equivalent Hit Dice. Treat such a creature&#8217;s Hit Dice as equal to its CR x 2 + the number of cohort Hit Dice added to it for the purpose of determining the number of Hit Dice required from your Hit Dice pool.</p>\n<p>Creatures that advance by Hit Dice may do so whenever the cohort would normally be allowed to advance, but cannot exceed the normal limits on effective Hit Dice. Intelligent creatures that you create, such as via the Bestow Life advanced talent of the Enhancement sphere or the Greater Undead advanced talent of the Death sphere, are usually willing to serve as advanced cohorts, removing the +10 DC increase for having a different type.</p>\n","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[["Cohort"]],"activation":{"cost":1,"type":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","long":null},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null,"autoDeductCharges":true,"autoDeductChargesCost":"1"},"measureTemplate":{"type":"","size":"0","overrideColor":false,"customColor":"","overrideTexture":false,"customTexture":""},"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","critConfirmBonus":"","damage":{"parts":[],"critParts":[],"nonCritParts":[]},"attackParts":[],"formula":"","ability":{"attack":null,"damage":null,"damageMult":1,"critRange":20,"critMult":2},"save":{"dc":0,"type":"","description":""},"effectNotes":"","attackNotes":"","soundEffect":"","changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noStr":false,"noDex":false,"oneInt":false,"oneWis":false,"oneCha":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[],"charges":[]},"featType":"combatTalent","associations":{"classes":[]},"showInQuickbar":false,"abilityType":"none","crOffset":"","attack":{"parts":[]},"sphere":"Leadership","identifiedName":"Advanced Cohorts"},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.V5hGX6Y6zlIjqj8b"},"spheres-sheet":{"sphere":"SpheresSheet.SphereLeadership"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"hMMlShyz5bIaecay","name":"Discern Illusions","permission":{"default":0,"55oRMeK8J5d3pvei":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>As long as you have martial focus, you gain a bonus to all Will saves against illusions (including glamers, figments, and any effects created by the illusion school or the Illusion sphere) equal to 1/2 your ranks in Perception (minimum 1). As a swift action, you can expend martial focus to share this bonus with all allies within 30 ft. for a number of rounds equal to your practitioner modifier.</p>\n","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"activation":{"cost":1,"type":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","long":null},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null,"autoDeductCharges":true,"autoDeductChargesCost":"1"},"measureTemplate":{"type":"","size":"0","overrideColor":false,"customColor":"","overrideTexture":false,"customTexture":""},"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","critConfirmBonus":"","damage":{"parts":[],"critParts":[],"nonCritParts":[]},"attackParts":[],"formula":"","ability":{"attack":null,"damage":null,"damageMult":1,"critRange":20,"critMult":2},"save":{"dc":0,"type":"","description":""},"effectNotes":"","attackNotes":"","soundEffect":"","changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noStr":false,"noDex":false,"oneInt":false,"oneWis":false,"oneCha":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[],"charges":[]},"featType":"combatTalent","associations":{"classes":[]},"showInQuickbar":false,"abilityType":"none","crOffset":"","attack":{"parts":[]},"sphere":"Scout","identifiedName":"Discern Illusions"},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.xwinZzr1zFbpKnkk"},"spheres-sheet":{"sphere":"SpheresSheet.SphereScout"}},"img":"modules/spheres-sheet/icons/spheres/scout.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"hScS5l2FhdqgpY8F","name":"Dual Attack","permission":{"default":0,"55oRMeK8J5d3pvei":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Whenever you make an attack action with a light or one-handed weapon, you can make an additional attack with a light or one-handed weapon held in your off-hand, though both attacks take a -2 penalty on their attack rolls when doing so; only your initial main hand attack qualifies as an attack action, and the additional attack cannot be made with the same weapon as your initial main hand attack. Your off-hand attack only applies 1/2 your Strength modifier, and if your off-hand attack is made with anything other than a light weapon, both attacks take an additional -2 penalty. <strong>Associated Feat:</strong> Two-Weapon Fighting</p>\n","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"activation":{"cost":1,"type":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","long":null},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null,"autoDeductCharges":true,"autoDeductChargesCost":"1"},"measureTemplate":{"type":"","size":"0","overrideColor":false,"customColor":"","overrideTexture":false,"customTexture":""},"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","critConfirmBonus":"","damage":{"parts":[],"critParts":[],"nonCritParts":[]},"attackParts":[],"formula":"","ability":{"attack":null,"damage":null,"damageMult":1,"critRange":20,"critMult":2},"save":{"dc":0,"type":"","description":""},"effectNotes":"","attackNotes":"","soundEffect":"","changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noStr":false,"noDex":false,"oneInt":false,"oneWis":false,"oneCha":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[],"charges":[]},"featType":"combatTalent","associations":{"classes":[]},"showInQuickbar":false,"abilityType":"none","crOffset":"","attack":{"parts":[]},"sphere":"Dual Wielding","identifiedName":"Dual Attack"},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.cO6p64mkMkGSL9fy"},"spheres-sheet":{"sphere":"SpheresSheet.SphereDualWielding"}},"img":"modules/spheres-sheet/icons/spheres/dual_wielding.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"hWdTMlo5jBusFBsZ","name":"Locust Pounce","permission":{"default":0,"55oRMeK8J5d3pvei":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You may roll an Acrobatics check to jump as part of a melee attack action, moving no more than half your land speed before performing the attack action. This movement is not subtracted from your total movement per round. You may expend your martial focus to make this movement without provoking an attack of opportunity.</p>\n","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[["Leap"]],"activation":{"cost":1,"type":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","long":null},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null,"autoDeductCharges":true,"autoDeductChargesCost":"1"},"measureTemplate":{"type":"","size":"0","overrideColor":false,"customColor":"","overrideTexture":false,"customTexture":""},"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","critConfirmBonus":"","damage":{"parts":[],"critParts":[],"nonCritParts":[]},"attackParts":[],"formula":"","ability":{"attack":null,"damage":null,"damageMult":1,"critRange":20,"critMult":2},"save":{"dc":0,"type":"","description":""},"effectNotes":"","attackNotes":"","soundEffect":"","changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noStr":false,"noDex":false,"oneInt":false,"oneWis":false,"oneCha":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[],"charges":[]},"featType":"combatTalent","associations":{"classes":[]},"showInQuickbar":false,"abilityType":"none","crOffset":"","attack":{"parts":[]},"sphere":"Athletics","identifiedName":"Locust Pounce"},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.pXhx0Fzfve2uUzPH"},"spheres-sheet":{"sphere":"SpheresSheet.SphereAthletics"}},"img":"modules/spheres-sheet/icons/spheres/athletics.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"hashztVUt8SJbuQ3","name":"Roaring Reservoir","permission":{"default":0,"55oRMeK8J5d3pvei":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You may use a shout that normally requires you to expend your martial focus without expending your martial focus, but doing so makes you fatigued for 1 minute. If you are already fatigued, you become exhausted for this duration instead. You cannot use this talent while exhausted.</p>\n","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"activation":{"cost":1,"type":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","long":null},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null,"autoDeductCharges":true,"autoDeductChargesCost":"1"},"measureTemplate":{"type":"","size":"0","overrideColor":false,"customColor":"","overrideTexture":false,"customTexture":""},"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","critConfirmBonus":"","damage":{"parts":[],"critParts":[],"nonCritParts":[]},"attackParts":[],"formula":"","ability":{"attack":null,"damage":null,"damageMult":1,"critRange":20,"critMult":2},"save":{"dc":0,"type":"","description":""},"effectNotes":"","attackNotes":"","soundEffect":"","changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noStr":false,"noDex":false,"oneInt":false,"oneWis":false,"oneCha":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[],"charges":[]},"featType":"combatTalent","associations":{"classes":[]},"showInQuickbar":false,"abilityType":"none","crOffset":"","attack":{"parts":[]},"sphere":"Warleader","identifiedName":"Roaring Reservoir"},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.aZUZpx3h9zRNysTa"},"spheres-sheet":{"sphere":"SpheresSheet.SphereWarleader"}},"img":"modules/spheres-sheet/icons/spheres/warleader.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"hk6cphCojG82k0aq","name":"Up, Down And","permission":{"default":0,"55oRMeK8J5d3pvei":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>While you have the drunk status, you eliminate the penalties to your armor class and melee attacks while prone. Additionally, if you strike an enemy while prone, and then attack them again within one round while standing (or vice versa), you can expend your martial focus to target their flat-footed armor class for the second attack.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> If you possess the Capoeira Spin talent from the Open Hand sphere, you always eliminate all penalties from being prone rather than only when drunk, and you can stand up without provoking attacks of opportunity as a free action made as part of an attack action while you have the drunk status, rather than an immediate action. At +10 base attack bonus, you instead gain a +2 bonus to attack rolls made while prone.</p>\n","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"activation":{"cost":1,"type":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","long":null},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null,"autoDeductCharges":true,"autoDeductChargesCost":"1"},"measureTemplate":{"type":"","size":"0","overrideColor":false,"customColor":"","overrideTexture":false,"customTexture":""},"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","critConfirmBonus":"","damage":{"parts":[],"critParts":[],"nonCritParts":[]},"attackParts":[],"formula":"","ability":{"attack":null,"damage":null,"damageMult":1,"critRange":20,"critMult":2},"save":{"dc":0,"type":"","description":""},"effectNotes":"","attackNotes":"","soundEffect":"","changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noStr":false,"noDex":false,"oneInt":false,"oneWis":false,"oneCha":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[],"charges":[]},"featType":"combatTalent","associations":{"classes":[]},"showInQuickbar":false,"abilityType":"none","crOffset":"","attack":{"parts":[]},"sphere":"Barroom","identifiedName":"Up, Down And"},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Q5912QWvyuM0aR6k"},"spheres-sheet":{"sphere":"SpheresSheet.SphereBarroom"}},"img":"modules/spheres-sheet/icons/spheres/barroom.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"hkSHVbfC0yXA4BZf","name":"Net","permission":{"default":0,"55oRMeK8J5d3pvei":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>When used with a dart trap, a creature that is struck by your dart must make a Reflex save or become entangled. You may forgo damage to resolve this attack against touch AC. This condition lasts until the creature succeeds on a Strength or Escape Artist check against the trap&#8217;s DC or destroys the trap via damage.</p>\n<p>When used with a snare trap, the target is entangled and unable to move from the triggering square until it succeeds on a Strength or Escape Artist check against the trap&#8217;s DC or destroys the trap via damage.</p>\n","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[["Dart"],["Snare"]],"activation":{"cost":1,"type":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","long":null},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null,"autoDeductCharges":true,"autoDeductChargesCost":"1"},"measureTemplate":{"type":"","size":"0","overrideColor":false,"customColor":"","overrideTexture":false,"customTexture":""},"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","critConfirmBonus":"","damage":{"parts":[],"critParts":[],"nonCritParts":[]},"attackParts":[],"formula":"","ability":{"attack":null,"damage":null,"damageMult":1,"critRange":20,"critMult":2},"save":{"dc":0,"type":"","description":""},"effectNotes":"","attackNotes":"","soundEffect":"","changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noStr":false,"noDex":false,"oneInt":false,"oneWis":false,"oneCha":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[],"charges":[]},"featType":"combatTalent","associations":{"classes":[]},"showInQuickbar":false,"abilityType":"none","crOffset":"","attack":{"parts":[]},"sphere":"Trap","identifiedName":"Net"},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.4BmAJEUE04AhFlx0"},"spheres-sheet":{"sphere":"SpheresSheet.SphereTrap"}},"img":"modules/spheres-sheet/icons/spheres/trap.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"hoimHVOLBIBmTAG2","name":"Punishing Challenge","permission":{"default":0,"55oRMeK8J5d3pvei":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Guardian sphere, base attack bonus +5.</p>\n<p>Whenever a creature affected by your challenge makes an attack roll or casts a non-harmless spell that does not target you or include you in its effect, that creature takes untyped damage equal to your base attack bonus. This damage is not subject to resistance or damage reduction. This is a supernatural effect.</p>\n","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"activation":{"cost":1,"type":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","long":null},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null,"autoDeductCharges":true,"autoDeductChargesCost":"1"},"measureTemplate":{"type":"","size":"0","overrideColor":false,"customColor":"","overrideTexture":false,"customTexture":""},"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","critConfirmBonus":"","damage":{"parts":[],"critParts":[],"nonCritParts":[]},"attackParts":[],"formula":"","ability":{"attack":null,"damage":null,"damageMult":1,"critRange":20,"critMult":2},"save":{"dc":0,"type":"","description":""},"effectNotes":"","attackNotes":"","soundEffect":"","changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noStr":false,"noDex":false,"oneInt":false,"oneWis":false,"oneCha":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[],"charges":[]},"featType":"combatTalent","associations":{"classes":[]},"showInQuickbar":false,"abilityType":"none","crOffset":"","attack":{"parts":[]},"sphere":"Guardian","identifiedName":"Punishing Challenge"},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.QSnY2bd0jdT3GqJ6"},"spheres-sheet":{"sphere":"SpheresSheet.SphereGuardian"}},"img":"modules/spheres-sheet/icons/spheres/guardian.png","effects":[]}
